included.description:
The Internet can be a wonderful resource for kids. They can use it to research school reports, communicate with teachers and other kids, and play interactive games. But that access can also pose hazards. Hence it becomes important to be aware of what kids see and hear on the Internet, who they meet, and what they share about themselves online. 
The goal of this research is to develop an understanding of how elementary school kids perceive online safety on their mobile devices.Â â

included.summary:
Hi! I am a User Experience Designer and Researcher. I am working at Cvent as a User Research Assistant. At work, I enjoy working with data sets, performing qualitative analysis, design thinking and problem solving and visualizing data to make it easily absorbable and pretty!  I am also a graduate student at the University of Maryland studying Human Computer Interaction. 
I work towards making products intuitive, easy to use and  eliminating all the possible pain points users encounter. I believe a good design needs no manual and I dream of a world without manuals and frustrations! 

Apart from my professional interests, I love dancing, learning new dance styles and eating pizza!
included.headline: User Research Assistant at Cvent

included.description: The aim of this project was to design and build a user-friendly technology for the Ghostbusters. We decided to make an improved version of the already existing PKE meter. This device helps the Ghostbusters to detect ghosts.
included.title: Ghostbusters

included.description: Pratham is a Non profit organisation working in India with a mandate of giving every child the Right to Education and assurance for Quality education . I have been associated with the organisation for a few years as a volunteer, assisting the organisation in data analysis in studies related to children's performances and in documentation of children's learning achievement from a Non reader to Reader . Writing case studies of children who were rescued from being child labourers and mainstreamed in schools, was also an experience that helped me understand and study this subject closely. Besides this , we also conducted group activities for children and held personality development sessions for them.
